# AsyncThrowingStream.Continuation.YieldResult.terminated

**Case**

The stream didn’t enqueue the element because the stream was in a terminal state.

## Declaration

```swift
case terminated
```

## Discussion

This indicates the stream terminated prior to calling `yield`, either because the stream finished normally or through cancellation, or it threw an error.

## Yield Results

- **AsyncThrowingStream.Continuation.YieldResult.enqueued(remaining:)**: The stream successfully enqueued the element.
- **AsyncThrowingStream.Continuation.YieldResult.dropped(_:)**: The stream didn’t enqueue the element because the buffer was full.
